<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8" standalone="no"?><?Xpress productLine="ncc-part" ?><part xmlns:xt="urn:xpressauthor:trackchanges" id="_ec0ebc74-a071-443f-8c89-69eea67e5077" outputclass="ncc-part"><num>H8</num><title id="_a556b323-9d9e-4bd7-93fb-112f97b16466">Livable housing design</title><part-variation deleted-text="This Part has deliberately been left blank. Part H8 does not apply in NSW, as livable housing design requirements do not apply to Class 1a buildings in NSW." variation="NSW" variation-type="DELETE">NSW DELETE Part</part-variation><intro-part id="_0a632d67-00f9-4d11-88ba-5e0c27cd376e"><p>This Part sets out requirements for dwellings to include features that are designed to improve their accessibility and usability for occupants and visitors, including those with a mobility-related disability.</p></intro-part><callout id="_2eceaa64-0a3b-4380-acf6-197dc818b218"><callout-type ncc-info-type="notes"/><title id="_13cde10d-ff1a-4a8a-a7ef-22eae669d509">Tasmania Part H8 Livable housing design</title><p>For Tasmania, refer to the Director’s Determination regarding the application of Part H8 (Livable housing provisions) of the NCC—current version available at <xref format="html" href="Consumer Building and Occupational Services (cbos.tas.gov.au).gov.au" id="_6de49d5b-f3cd-4be8-a2ab-947b66d5e055" scope="local">www.cbos.tas.gov.au</xref>.</p></callout><subtopic id="_dc6e805c-29eb-498e-aed7-23f5a7545f71" subtopic-type="objective"><clauseref id="_b89e6419-25a1-4bdc-bd8e-6be1bdcf7dc1" outputclass="clausref-ncc"><clause author="Kieran O'Donnell" conref="/tmp/QppServer/Publishing/8bd50c59-637c-4a79-8565-09cd674ed7ed/4929_0.5.0.xml" dateTime="2021-03-22T16:43:31" id="_1e1e0373-2658-43c8-a3c8-4b79bb38b62d" outputclass="ncc-clause" type="insert"><meta xmlns:inv="urn:xpressauthor:xpressdocument" inv:access="external"><facet building="Class 2" inv:access="external"/><facet building="Class 3" inv:access="external"/><facet building="Class 4" inv:access="external"/><facet bu